<article class='container container--article article-content two-column'>

<div class='main main-column'>
<div class='short-explanation'>
When a verb ends in 〜させる, it tells us that someone is forced to do the action, or allowed to do the action, depending on context. For this reason, 〜させる is known as the causative form.
</div>
<h2 id="table-of-contents">Table of Contents</h2>
<ul id="markdown-toc">
